examples.en: She verbally assaulted one of her coworkers.

The budding romance between the coworkers was the talk of the office.

She was offended by the profane language that her coworkers used so casually.
She estranged several of her coworkers when she let her promotion go to her head.
His coworkers knew him as Robert, but his intimates called him Robbie.
The department telltale told the boss that his coworkers were taking extra long breaks.
He tends to use too much hacker's slang when talking to coworkers about their computer problems.
He is a coworker of mine.
My coworker is a spy for the boss.
The rules prohibit dating a coworker.
He had a romantic relationship with a coworker.
He was fired for making lascivious remarks to a coworker.

That coworker would be easier to get along with if she weren't so testy all the time.

A nosy coworker sat down right next to us as we were having an unmistakably private conversation.
